Divine Patronage

Patronage lets a player pledge to Mitra, Gaea, or Set. A pledge affects the
rate at which heroes build Wrathful Avatar charge.

Use:

  patron
  patron gods
  patron pledge <mitra|gaea|set>
  patron renounce
  patron favor
  patron pilgrimage start
  patron pilgrimage status

Your patron rank rises as you earn favor. Favor comes from patron activity such
as tithes, shrines, pilgrimages, marked enemies, and deeds whose reputation
matches your patron. The exact favor numbers are hidden, but patron favor
describes your broad standing.

Each rank grants an avatar charge-rate bonus. If your patron is ascendant, the
bonus is stronger. During your patron's Holy Hour it is stronger again.

Mitra rewards fellowship. Mitra followers gain a small extra charge-rate bonus
for nearby Mitra followers in the same room.

Gaea rewards endurance. Gaea's blessing is weaker at full health and becomes
strongest when your health is low.

Set rewards shadow and pressure. When Set is ascendant, good-aligned non-Set
followers may suffer a charge-rate penalty unless protected by special events
or shrine actions.

Renouncing a patron leaves a temporary debt that slows Wrathful Avatar charge.
Use score or meter to see your current charge rate.

The patron command also shows Signs. Signs describe whether your recent
reputation fits your pledge or strains it. A strained vow can briefly slow
Wrathful Avatar charge, but it does not remove your patron.

Patron activity:

  Tithes       Offer coins with tithe <amount> to <god>, or tithe at shrine.
  Shrines      Pray or tithe at a divine shrine.
  Pilgrimage   Start with patron pilgrimage start after pledging.
  Combat       Marked enemies may appear as the divine cycle stirs.

Shrines can currently be found at:

  Mitra  The Temple of Mitra in DarkWind City.
  Gaea   The rose garden near the chapel.
  Set    The black altar in the temple of Qazaash.

